All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
AdminController
AdminController class represents all functionality for the Admin Subsystem.
Album
Album class contains String Name, ArrayList Photos, int numOfPhotos, SimpleDateFormat oldestDate, SimpleDateFormat newestDate, String coverpath as attributes.
AlbumPageController
AlbumPageController class represents the functionality for the Album Page.
CreateTagController
CreateTagController represents the functionality for the user's Create Tag Page.
CustomTags
CustomTags class is a subclass of Tags class.
InsideAlbumController
InsideAlbumController class provides all of the functionality of the page that a user enters once they have chosen an Album to open, Inside Album Page.
insideSRController
insideSRController class provides the functionality for the user with the resulting photo results from the preceding photos search.
LoginController
LoginController represents the functionality for the Login Page.
Logout
Logout class contains logout() method that saves the information of the current user's session and returns the user to the Login scene.
Photo
toString() method returns a formatted String of tag name, tag type on a single line, in a format that can be printed next to its respective Photo
Photos
Photos class extends application with start method and main method to start the application.
searchController
searchController class provides all of the functionality for users to search through their Albums for any photos with a user-input date range or set of tag-value pairs.
Tags
Tags class represents Tag objects with attributes of Strings for the tag type and tag name, and implements Serializable so that the tags remain associated to their respective photos across sessions.
User
User class creates instance of User object with constructor.
Users
Users class is comprised of an ArrayList of users that remains static and implements Serializable so that the list of users carries through all sessions.
